{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44267656-73d6-48ec-845e-c8cb11f3a4bd","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support entirely.** Starting with v4.0, the SDK only ships the **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)** runner. The VSTest adapter is no longer included, so `vstest.console` can't discover or run your tests.\n\n### What to do\n\n| Option | How |\n|---|---|\n| **Migrate to `dotnet test`** | `dotnet test` works with MTP out of the box — no `vstest.console` needed. |\n| **Stay on VSTest temporarily** | Pin to `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.x` and set `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` in your project. |\n\nThe recommended path is to replace `vstest.console` invocations in your CI pipeline with `dotnet test`, which automatically uses the new platform when targeting MSTest.Sdk 4.x.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6ba46b66-e20c-4323-a39e-0e1e49ce8256","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nLet me look at the files in the current directory to understand the context better, but this is primarily a knowledge-based question.\n\nKey change: Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, Microsoft introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (MTP) as the default test runner. However, the critical breaking change is that **MSTest.Sdk 3.x** still supported VSTest by default (or had it as an option), while **MSTest.Sdk 4.x** dropped VSTest support entirely or changed the default.\n\n\nActually, let me clarify the progression more precisely. In 3.3 and later, MTP became the default runner, but you could still opt into VSTest through project file settings like `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`. That option remained available through 3.8, but in 4.0 and beyond, that configuration property was removed entirely, eliminating VSTest compatibility altogether.\n\nThe core problem is that `vstest.console` depends on the VSTest adapter being present in the test assemblies. Once MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support, those adapter components disappeared, leaving `vstest.console` unable to discover any tests.\n\nTo resolve this, I can either migrate to `dotnet test` with the appropriate adapter paths or the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform CLI, or revert to an earlier MSTest.Sdk version that still supports VSTest. Let me look at what's in the directory to understand the current setup better.","outputTokens":718,"requestId":"7C10:203FDB:2D7F434:32A54BE:69F96026"},"id":"f3cc2f78-340f-4460-948c-daa1da39abcc","timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:12:53.759Z","parentId":"2cbdce52-c3d7-43e0-9784-929caf1cf736"}
